item.title: A comic for your reading pleasure
item.dc:creator: BrAndi
item.description:
Very interesting in terms of graphic novel theory: you break the rules of the still image. By not knowing which frame is movable and which isn’t you can instill certain emotions better. I recommend using louder sounds as well for certrain frames. That way the readers fantasy fills the gaps and the reader enters the story quicker, whereas the shocking moments can be made more shocking by really showing and playing back certain things.
